ment and student debt to show how youth issues are highly politicized, looking at specific, recent uprisings such as the Arab Spring in which youth have played a central role. Through a rigorous theoretical study that is both global and multidisciplinary in scope, Youth Rising? ultimately draws conclusions about the relationship between youth and social change"--cProvided by publisher.  a43 0aYouthxPolitical activity. 0aYoung adultsxPolitical activity. 0aYouth movements. 0aPolitical participation. 0aCapitalism. 0aSocial justice. 0aYouthxEmployment. 0aYoung adultsxEmployment. 0aStudent loans.1 aTannock, Stuart,d1969-eauthor. 0aCritical youth studies.  aHQ 799.2 P6 S85 2014c1hUAHS-Bi0162035190360  aHQ 799.2 P6 S85 2014wLCc1i0162035190360d1/31/2017e1/31/2017kCHECKEDOUTlON_SHELFmUAHSSn5p$150.00rMsYtBOOKu11/26/201401ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n00098974bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/45538678